<TITLE> Ex-police official charged with fraud </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Sept 20 (bdnews24.com)  Former additional inspector general of police (IGP) Shahidullah Khan Thursday was charged with fraud to get a plot in the port city. Chittagong Development Authority (CDA) secretary Anisuzzaman filed the case against the former police official with Kotwali Police Station. Officer in charge of the police station Haniful Islam told bdnews24.com the case alleged that in his days as police commissioner in Chittagong Khan had taken allotment of a plot though he had another plot. Islam said sub-inspector Prodip Kumar Das has been put on the case. Das said the CDA secretary alleged Khan had claimed in an affidavit he did not have any plot or land in Chittagong while taking allotment of a plot in Kalpolok residential area. On the affidavit he was allotted a plot in the area in 2006. But investigation revealed that he had a plot in Panchlaish cooperative society in another residential area under CDA, Das said. bdnews
